  "id": "volatility_contraction_trend_strategy",
  "name": "Volatility Contraction Trend Strategy",
  "description": "This trend-following strategy identifies breakout opportunities by analyzing the contraction of Bollinger Bands. It focuses on periods where the bands narrow significantly, signaling a potential volatility squeeze, and enters long positions when the price closes above the upper band.",
  "algorithm_type": "TrendFollowing",
  "prompt": "Create a trend-following breakout strategy that operates on daily bars and uses volatility contraction as a setup. Calculate the 14-day Bollinger Bands (2 standard deviations) and measure their width. Look for periods where the Bollinger Bands width contracts to the lowest 10% of values measured over the past 120 days, signaling a volatility squeeze. Enter a long position when price closes above the upper Bollinger Band during or immediately after a squeeze, confirmed by daily volume exceeding its 30-day moving average. Enter a short position if price closes below the lower Bollinger Band with the same volume confirmation. Exit the trade if price crosses back inside the Bollinger Bands or after 10 bars, whichever comes first.",
